<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having a pouch for carrying the
immature young; of or pertaining to the Marsupialia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat. & Zool.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to a
marsupium; <as>as, the <ex>marsupial</ex> bones</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Marsupial frog</b></col>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>See
<er>Nototrema</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>marsupial</ent>⟦br⟧

